tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE lead_sources (
 lead_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
 source_name VARCHAR(50),
 channel_type VARCHAR(50),
 lead_quality VARCHAR(20),
 conversion_rate DECIMAL(5,2)
);

CREATE TABLE lead_sources (
  lead_source_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  lead_source_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
  lead_channel_type VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
  lead_conversion_rate DECIMAL(5,2) NOT NULL
)

CREATE TABLE lead_analysis (
  analysis_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  lead_source_id INT,
  lead_date DATE NOT NULL,
  lead_count INT NOT NULL,
  lead_conversion_rate DECIMAL(5,2) NOT NULL,
  FOREIGN KEY (lead_source_id) REFERENCES lead_sources(lead_source_id)
)

CREATE TABLE lead_generation (
    lead_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    source_id INT, 
    lead_date DATE NOT NULL,
    lead_status VARCHAR(20) NOT NULL,
    lead_value DECIMAL(10,2),
    FOREIGN KEY (source_id) REFERENCES lead_sources(source_id) ON DELETE CASCADE
);

CREATE TABLE LeadSources (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    source_name VARCHAR(255),
    campaign_name VARCHAR(255),
    cost DECIMAL(10,2),
    created_at TIMESTAMP
);

CREATE TABLE MarketingChannels (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    channel_name VARCHAR(255),
    channel_type VARCHAR(50),
    description TEXT,
    created_at TIMESTAMP
);

CREATE TABLE Leads (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    lead_name VARCHAR(255),
    lead_email VARCHAR(255),
    phone_number VARCHAR(15),
    lead_source_id INT,
    created_at TIMESTAMP
);

CREATE TABLE LeadAnalytics (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    lead_id INT,
    conversion_rate DECIMAL(5,2),
    conversion_status BOOLEAN,
    analytics_data JSON,
    created_at TIMESTAMP
);

CREATE TABLE lead_generation (
    generation_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    lead_id INT,
    channel_id INT,
    generated_date DATE,
    conversion_status BOOLEAN
);

CREATE TABLE campaign_performance (
    campaign_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    channel_id INT,
    start_date DATE,
    end_date DATE,
    total_leads_generated INT,
    conversion_rate DECIMAL(5,2)
);
